lmao mediapipe is awesome, are there any other lightweight models used to track the face? i was thinking i could use that an overlay like a zuko scar on my face lmfao
ChatGPT said:
Haha, that would be awesome—and yes, MediaPipe Face Mesh is perfect for this! It’s lightweight, real-time, and tracks 468 face landmarks (eyes, nose, mouth, jawline, etc.), making it easy to overlay graphics like a Zuko scar.

Lightweight Face Tracking Models
MediaPipe Face Mesh

Detects 468 detailed 3D face landmarks.

Runs on-device in real-time (even on phones).

Perfect for AR filters (like Instagram/Snapchat).

MediaPipe Face Detection

Simpler, just detects face bounding boxes (no detailed landmarks).

Even faster but not great for overlays like scars.

ARCore Augmented Faces (Google ARCore)

ARCore’s face API provides face regions (forehead, nose, cheeks).

Heavier than MediaPipe and requires ARCore-supported devices.

BlazeFace (MediaPipe)

Ultra-lightweight 2D face landmark model (only ~6 landmarks).

Great for basic overlays like masks but not detailed scars.

Your Zuko Scar Idea
With MediaPipe Face Mesh, you can:

Detect face landmarks.

Find the exact coordinates of where Zuko’s scar should be (left eye + cheek area).

Overlay a PNG image or draw directly on a Canvas to place the scar in real-time.

