You said:
oh mediapipe has face detection too?
ChatGPT said:
Yes! MediaPipe has multiple face-related solutions, not just hand or body tracking. In fact, it has two main face modules:

1. MediaPipe Face Detection
Lightweight & Fast: Detects just the face bounding box (and key features like eyes and mouth) in real-time.

Best for simple use cases like verifying if a face is present or framing a selfie camera.

Similar to a standard "face detector" — doesn't give detailed points for overlays.

2. MediaPipe Face Mesh
Advanced model: Tracks 468 detailed 3D landmarks on the face (eyes, lips, cheeks, jaw, etc.).

Perfect for AR filters, makeup effects, or adding something like your Zuko scar idea.

Still lightweight enough to run on mobile in real-time.

Which One to Use?
If you just need to detect "is there a face here?" → Use Face Detection (lighter, faster).

If you need precise positioning (like scars, glasses, masks) → Use Face Mesh.

