In the [sample code](https://google.github.io/mediapipe/solutions/hands.html#python) the handedness is printed this way:
` print('handedness:', results.multi_handedness)`
however this returns a string, and I cannot find a way to access the displayed fields: index, score and label, any tips?

`results.multi_handedness` is a `mediapipe.framework.formats.classification_pb2.ClassificationList` object, which is not iterable?

Thanks! :)
